CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1940, reads: "Notables Of Nation Discuss Defense Participation At Hampton Conference - Approximately 350 white and colored leaders gathered at Hampton institute last Monday and Tuesday for the inauguration of Hampton's sixth president, Dr. Malcolm MacLean, and to take part in Conference for the Participation of Negroes in National Defense. Defense activity was divided into 11 sections.  Some of those who made contributions to the discussions, caught by Staff Photographer Harris, are shown above....6. Mrs. Charles H. Houston of Washington, D.C...."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Charles H. Houston of Washington, D.C., standing beside horse and rider statue in interior at Hampton Institute
